<script src="/wp-content/uploads/js/chartjs-adapter-date-fns.bundle.js"></script>

<div id="all-episodes" style="height: 300px;"></div>
<script>
    new Chartkick.ColumnChart("all-episodes", [
        {% for episode in podcast.episodes({publicationDate: 'title', 'order': 'ASC'})|filter(e => e.total_downloads > 0) %}
            ["{{ episode.title|split(' ')|first|escape('js') }}", {{ episode.total_downloads|escape('js') }}],
        {% endfor %}
    ]);
</script>

<p></p>
<p>Gezählt werden <a href="https://docs.podlove.org/podlove-publisher/reference/download-analytics">Downloadversuche</a>. Hinzu kommen nach zwei Wochen etwa <b>250 <a href="https://support.spotifyforpodcasters.com/hc/de/articles/360043988952-Daten-zu-begonnenen-Wiedergaben-und-Streams">Streams</a> auf Spotify</b>.</p>

<h3>Unsere beliebtesten Folgen</h3>
<ul>
    {% for episode in podcast.episodes|filter(e => e.total_downloads > 0)|sort((b, a) => a.total_downloads <=> b.total_downloads)|slice(0,5) %}
        <li>
            <a href="{{ episode.url }}"><b>{{ episode.title|split(' - ')|first }}</b></a> ({{ episode.total_downloads }} Downloads)
        </li>
    {% endfor %}
</ul>

